<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="664" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d664">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3682: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Poole</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-24T14:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 24,
                                        1919, 2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Telegraph American Mission Paris and Department at once answers to
                                following:<note n="4" xml:id="d664fn4">For answers see telegrams
                                from the Chargé in Russia, no. 793, Jan. 27, 3 p.m., <ref target="#pg_608">p. 608</ref>, no. 794, Jan. 27, 4 p.m., <ref target="#pg_610">p. 610</ref>, and no. 812, Jan, 30, 5 p.m.,
                                    <ref target="#pg_37">p. 37</ref>.</note> “1st, what is present
                            attitude of the Russians towards Allied intervention? 2d, what is the
                            attitude of the Archangel Government toward <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>? 3d, what are plans of Archangel Government for
                            spring campaign? 4th, to what extent is present Government supported in
                            and outside Archangel?</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>